{"IName_input":"Body of Sunset","IType_input":"component","WType_input":"","WDmg_input":"","Desc1_input":"This is a part of the legendary Sunset rifle, a fabled weapon forged long ago as a tool for wielding light against the darkness. Also known as 'radiant piercer', it did greater damage the further the targets alignment was from lawful good.","Desc2_input":"The Sunset was last rumoured to have been wielded by a great elven hero Alaine Greenleaf, but was feared too powerful and split into three pieces.","Desc3_input":"This is the body, a blend of ornate gold metal work and hand carved wood, laden with ornate cyan jewels. The body has a perfectly cut channel to receive the barrel and a forward bracket to receive some form of sight. The trigger system requires no adjustments, working perfectly, as if it were just made yesterday.","Source_input":"Homebrew."}